reviews.text: Love this Starbucks! They always get my order correct and are super friendly! I rarely deviate from my usual Mocha Cookie Frappuccino so it’s pretty neat when they recognize me or know me by name based on my recurring order.  This store is my happy place!

This has been my go-to location for about a year. Initially, they made my iced shaken espresso with way too much foam that they didn't scoop out to pour the actual drink to a legitimage venti size that I was paying for, but eventually, they got there for about 80% of the time I visit.

They're quick and efficient. Very friendly from when I go at 6am, or if I go at 6pm. I recommend this location despite the disaster of parking.
Stopped in for a drink. Staff was nice. I hope that Starbuck's corporate pays their employees more money and give them better benefits so they don't have to strike.
Got a pumpkin spice latter just now and for some reason it tastes like soap!? So far it’s been less than mediocre coffee. Not sure if it’s the employees or just the quality of coffee detonating

Alexis did way too much talking with her coworkers which caused me to have to wait 20 mins to order. There was only one other customer in the store at the time. There was no reason for the delay. She didn’t even apologize for the wait.

Something different for a change. Food was delicious, flavorful and the drinks were strong!! I had the chicken shawarmaand that was really good while my friend and the lamb.  Five minutes wait on a walk-in. We were seated outside in tent since the inside was reserved for private party. Good thing the weather wasn't too bad on a Saturday. They do offer hookah at your table as well.

We enjoy the food every time I come here for lunch! We usually order a variety of appetizers to share “tapas style,” and everything we try is always delicious! Plenty of outdoor seating and friendly staff!

My first visit was there. Nice ambiance. Staffs were very friendly and helpful.
The food was too small in quantity compared to price. Everything was very expensive. Food taste is moderate.

This is a very nice place if you’re craving Lebanese food!

I ordered the shish tawouk shawerma combo that came with fries and a soda. It was really delicious.

I did ask for some pickles and they charged me $6 for it.

Our waitress was clearly new and she was little overwhelmed and all over the place. Even though me and my friend asked for 2 separate checks, we had to return the bill two times because the orders on the bill were mixed up.

All in all, I liked the food and atmosphere of the restaurant. I recommend sitting outside if you’re visiting; they have a nice outside seating area.
Great service, lovely inside room and very spacious they have outside sitting very big as well. Food was delicious and great service.

The brick-oven pizza is pretty good here. I've been here a few times but the last couple of times the crust came out a bit doughy for me so I asked if they would make it extra crispy and it came out perfect.

It was a Sunday and lots of games on with a table next to us watching a game on their phone very loudly. I was not expecting the sports bar feel but that's what we got. As long as you know that going in it's not too bad but if you want a quiet afternoon or evening out this may not be the venue for you.

I still gave a 4 out of 5 star because the food was good, the service decent, and the atmosphere okay once you understand what you're getting.

The pizza was delicious! Try it for yourself 👍🏽However, don’t order hummus for takeout. $8 for a less than half full container is not worth it. Not sure how many ounces it comes with, but an appropriate size container would be nice. Thanks again for the yummy pizza.

We were in town for my father's burial with family. George helped me plan a wonderful dinner for everyone to be together after. The food and service was absolutely wonderful. When we are back in the area we will definitely be back.

came by after watching a movie. was able to be seated quickly. service was overall good. the reason I did 4 vs 5 stars is because they were missing some items even though they were listed on their menu and then the food not have much taste. my wife had to get a jalapeno flavored drink it was later told that they didn't have any jalapenos so they couldn't make the drink. when she asks could they make the drink without the jalapenos the bartender stated that he would not do it because it would not taste good without the jalapenos however he did not make any additional recommendations for substitute drink that will give her the taste she was looking for. next I bought the lamb meal with the rice. no matter how much salt or pepper I put on it it didn't have much taste so I pretty much did not eat it.

The lamb sliders and brussel sprouts were good well at least the first round of lamb sliders. We really liked them so ordered more but it's like the cook forgot how they should be made in just that short period of time. The HH prices are great tho. We both had HH drink specials but my wife didn't really like hers, mine was decent . The bar area is super small so ppl were kind of on each other which sucked but we will def give it another go.

The food here is outstanding! We are impressed by how flavorful all the dishes are and very happy with the portion sizes and friendly service.  The fried rice was the best I've ever had and my "white rice only" husband even stole half the carton for himself.  The general tso chicken is really amazing- slightly spicy and very flavorful with good big pieces of chicken.  The egg rolls and spring rolls were crispy and full of filling. It's great to finally have found a "go-to" Chinese carryout!

Do not order online from new China taste. My GF and I have had 3 credit cards comprised right after placing an order online. American Express just confirmed this. However, the food is good. Just pay in cash!

Best Chinese food in town.  Amazing chicken and broccoli and their shrimp fried rice is just amazing.  We are picking with our Chinese food, and only order from this place, because they are that good.

- Staff was friendly

- place was clean

- food was really good

- prices not bad

- service was quick

- this is a mostly just a take out place,  very small on the inside and only has a single table

- overall a good place, I'd recommend it

Love the friendliness, quick service, and delicious food!! Very seldom do you order take out and have it arrive too hot to eat- however that’s my experience every time here! Taking one star off because my credit card gets compromised every time I order from their website :(

SO SO GOOD!!  I love me some yellow curry and they have some of the best I’ve ever had! Our waiter was so helpful and attentive. I live in the pacific north west or I’d frequent the hell out of this place. If you like Thai you should eat here. Even if you don’t…you should give them a try!

Came here during a drop off to college and it was a nice find.  Thw Drunken Noodles were super hot and had a really good bite of spices.  The spicy beef salad (sorry forgot the menu name)  was also really good.  The restaurant it self is quite large I can see it getting very busy during the business week at lunch time.

A friend and I walked in this winter and found it to be a great lunch. I shared I had gluten intolerance and three staff members consulted for my meal. There is no allergen information listed on the menu, but there is a line about informing the server about dietary restrictions at the bottom of it. They were eager to make dietary accommodations to the existing menu: they made the tofu pad thai a gluten free entree and also edited the spring rolls for a gluten intolerant person: they removed the sausage and added more veggies and rice noodles. I also asked for hot water and my friend cold and they made sure to refill each with the right temps. I recommend diners enjoy Pasara Thai on their next opportunity.

Wow, really good! I just needed some good food after a long travel day and Thai sounded great. Couldn’t have asked for better food, ordered the Panang Chicken Curry and it was phenomenal. Flavors were on-point and the spice level was perfect. I can imagine some folks would think it too spicy and some not enough but it was perfectly balanced imo. Certainly worth stopping by, other options looked great too but my go-to is the Panang Chicken and it did not disappoint!

Currently on vacation and decided to try something different tonight. The hostess recommended the Pineapple Fried Rice and I can honestly say this is the best fried rice I've ever had! If I was staying longer, I'd come back. But the food and atmosphere is phenomenal! A+
It's improved now that they take coupons.  Typical subway with a good location.  Clean.  I have no complaints.
Great service. Ordered multiple subs and all were done correctly. Girls did a great job

I’m not sure if they just had a rough day or rushing to close but they were extremely rude, act like they didn’t know what I’m talking about when I asked for a kids meal and was overall just unfriendly, Not knowledgeable about their products and rude. Do better!

For some reason, the local Subways that are still open do not honor coupons that you may receive in the mail. Most often, you will not notice this until you happen to see a small, hand-written sign posted near the cash register. This policy is posted as a staff/food shortage response, so be aware. It's the reason why I stopped going to Subway.

Found a literal bone in the Chicken Wrap I got from here.

The end was so sharp it almost pierced the inside of my mouth.

Maybe make sure your chicken is deboned properly next time?
First time here and loved it.  Service was quick and got to see my food made.  Fries are amazing.  An order of a little fry is enough to feed a family of five.
Liked the bacon burger.  The Cajun fries are seriously good. The cost for 2 burgers and fries was $24. Seemed high to me.

Service was very slow for not being very busy. Food was good and hot but was very expensive for two hamburgers and an order of fries. One hamburger we ordered was incorrect. Ordered a single got a double and was charged for it as well.

A bit pricey for my budget but worth every ounce of meat in their burgers. I enjoyed that everything was fresh and cooked to perfection. I also had a milkshake and it was amazing. The wait staff was cordial and informative, and the food came out promptly. I cannot recommend it as a daily stop, but if you are craving for a tasty burger, this place certainly fits the bill.

$32 for 2 burgers, 1 fry, and 1 small coke. We won’t be back.

While good, this cost will never be justifiable.

I enjoyed having lunch here. The manager Tony was very helpful and patient with me. Make sure you ask for all the added fixings to your burger. If you just say a cheeseburger, they will give you bread, meat, and cheese only. The food is made on the spot, so be prepared for a small wait to get your food. Great lunch spot, but also has some beers and TVs for you to go later as well.

I should have asked for the staff's name that helped me.  Great service, loved the casual decor and open setting.  Would love to bring family here for group dinners.  I visited while on business travel on a weeknight.  I was very quiet with a few patrons at the bar.

I ordered a charburger with everything on it and side of onion rings.  The rings were hot temperature and tasty and not salty as other places.  I loved that the burger was topped with everything (too much pickle) and the bun kept it all together.  Bun was ok tasting, but it kept everything together and made it easy to eat.  Other places skimp on the bun and turns into a mess.

The service is casual and very friendly.  Food is served in baskets.  I assume they bus the tables since I did not see a trash and tray station.  Restaurant was clean and I saw staff clean the bar while I was there.

I would come back for a good burger (and service!).

Came here on Dec 11th with my bf and it was our first time. Definitely would recommend the service from Aaron was awesome he runs this place top notch. I got the grilled chicken sandwich and he got a burger and wings. Worth the cost for sure.

The empty glasses should explain it all. This place is GREAT. Good attentive staff who are also friendly and informative. The food was DELICIOUS 😋 and the scenery is very "chillaxed". I came in on a Saturday and they have optional seating. Come down and enjoy.

Pretty basic spot. Order at the counter and they bring the food out. Grilled burgers and did have a vegetarian and vegan burger option also. Parking lot is kinda janky. Had a regular burger and an impossible burger, both were good. Like that they are flame grilled and less greasy. Did not ask how we wanted them cooked so you get what you get. Not bad, expect $18 per person roughly for burger, fries and drink.

The pizza and papadia were good. A little bit soggy for both. Our first time to order the cheesesteak Parmesan crust papadia, and we love it; but the cheese was too runny or maybe juice from the beef. The pizza needed maybe additional minutes cooking. The toppings and cheese were sliding off the pizza. Over sauced maybe? We still enjoyed it. One of our favorite pizza brands, so we’ll be ordering again in the future.
They ask me to bring the pizza back to make new one?Really You think i’m going to drive 20 minutes to fix you’r mistake?0 customer service(missing piece and topping )

The worst Papa John's I have ever had! I ordered a meat lovers pizza original crust and I got a thin crust sausage and pepperoni. When I called, the manager said that's the way it comes. I travel for business and have purchased Papa John's from many locations and have never received such a disappointing experience ever. I would not recommend ordering from this location!
Awesome yummy pizza 🍕 😋 always friendly stuff
These guys have never messed up my order. The few times I got the 'wrong pizza' it was because I selected the wrong item from online ordering. Needless to say this is the go-to papa johns for me!

This is a fun, great location to take your young ones. I would have given a higher rating but I was very disappointed and perplexed by the Halloween decorations, Chuck E's demonic costume, and the witch casting spell songs that were constantly being played. This is very inappropriate for these young ones.

The pizza was good; staff was kind and helpful, and pricing is reasonable.
Thank you for hosting my grandbaby's 1st birthday! We had the best time and the staff was awesome! We will not forget this memorable moment! 🥳

I was impressed with how well the staff handled my son's birthday party. Malaika (our birthday rep) was great! She kept us informed from start to finish, and made sure we were on schedule and that everybody was having a good time. I highly recommend it for a child's birthday party!

This place is always to the Chucks E. Cheese standards.  It is a great place for the kids to play and have fun,  decent food,  and friendly employees.  In addition to a manager who always takes care of the issues.
We like going to this place and I recommend it.
Great experience! We celebrated my son birthday yesterday and everyone had a blast. The staff is very attentive. It was clean: Food was good!!

Beautiful place, enviable plants, nice atmosphere, reasonable food prices. Our server was attentive and accommodating. The drinks were a little overpriced for the food price point (3.50 for a cup of tea), but the fruit punch was awesome.

Nice dim ambiance. Honestly, i cannot believe i hadn’t reviewed this restaurant sooner. I discovered it about 7 or 8 years ago when i met my coworker who worked next door for lunch. I fell in love and have dined there ever since. The cuisine is so flavorful and arrives yo your table hot! When im in town and honestly desire a meal that wont let me down or satisfy my soul. Well, this is it! 🔥🔥🔥 I like to order the chicken and broccoli in oyster sauce or the thai basil fried rice. My family favorites are also the shrimp drunken noodle or Pad See-U and an order of spring rolls and the curry empanadas (the name escapes me) for appetizers. It is located close to the subway station. The surrounding area is developing and always seems to be under construction but grab a 1-hour parking spot out front if you can.
I purchased the Pad Thai w/ shrimp and beef medium spicy 🌶… it was delicious 😋… it did not take long to receive my order and their service is always friendly…

Great food for our party of three, everyone enjoyed. Service was prompt and very friendly! One note, we picked Galae because we were actually looking for sushi...yes, I know what the name is! There were some pics on here of sushi, and prior reviews mentioned sushi. Turns out they used to have sushi options on the menu but no longer. We were not at all disappointed though and will definitely be back.

Stopped by for appetizers, and we were not disappointed.  We ordered the puff pastry stuffed with chicken and potatoes, spring rolls, and the coconut curry and seafood soup. Everything was very good. The atmosphere was very nice and the service was good.
Not somewhere you'll get gourmet food or the freshest seafood but my first Cajun pasta experience was really tasty. Although the seafood on my plate was definitely frozen, they were generous with it.

WORST service I've ever had! Everything you ask it's a hard NO. Without confirming if it can be done. Manager is not warming at all - looks as if she doesn't want to be there. Margaritas are basically kool-aid. Don't waste your time. We picked over our COLD food. Jambalaya (or whatever it was) didn't have any sausage nor chicken. Just 4 shrimp on top! P.S. they'll charge you 18% service fee. 😒

They swore there was alcohol in the margaritas, but I’m pretty sure I paid $7 for a virgin beverage. I hoped the food would make up for the overpriced “happy hour” drink, but it reminded me of Mexican day at my college cafeteria. I should have expected a low quality experience when I read that they charge EVERYONE a default 18% gratuity. I get it when 8 or more people are splitting up a check. It’s easy to get stiffed, but when they charge solo diners the same, you know it’s because the food and service don’t warrant much of a tip.

Also, the place was empty when I came in and they seated another party right next to me. Even outside of the COVID era, this is inconsiderate. With so much space, why do they need us side-by-side? Especially since they have a loud baby.

The only reason I’m giving them 2 stars is that they did not add in gratuity for me. However the service, food, and “alcoholic” beverage were very low quality. I won’t be coming back.

Went for a quick happy hour. They have several flavors of margaritas that are delicious. I had shrimp tacos, the avocado sauce was divine! The waitress could have been a bit more attentive, but it was happy hour, I was really just there for the drinks.
I love the nachos from this place and the fact that they have happy hour everyday. Nachos are big enough to share.

Simply great!
I have some dietary restrictions and it was very easy to make some modifications so I could eat everything on my plate!
We waited a little bit to get our food but it was really worth it! The meat tasted great! The portions were big! The salmon was also super nicely cooked and tasty!
They have a lot of choices including a nice kids menu!
The service was great and friendly and the place super cozy!
The price is really good for what you get!
Really liked it!

I’m definitely in love with this place. While visiting from Michigan, we stopped in expecting something different due to the name “Bar and Grill” but this place can definitely be apart of fine dining. My boyfriend ordered a bison burger (not pictured) and I had the steak, that was cooked to perfection. They even serve homemade lemonade. The food was delicious and the service was warm and welcoming with no issues. Definitely will return in the near future.

Excellent restaurant. This was my second time and they are excellent. Delicious prime cuts. We have only tried the steaks.  Best cesar salad ever. The staff is very friendly.

Both times I have been there Sunday afternoon between 2 and 4 pm. Not too many people so it was easy to find a spot.  I don’t know how busy it is at other times.  Also they have one of the best classic margaritas.

Very good restaurant. I recommend it.

I had a fantastic experience here! The staff was terrific; some of the best people I’ve met during this trip to DC. This restaurant was recommended to me by a police officer in downtown Washington DC once he found out that I was staying in this area. I stopped here tonight, and it certainly didn’t disappoint; our waiter was exceptional, Juliet Cook, and the manager was delightful and accommodating, and amiable. The food was everything that I could have asked for and more.  Yonas our server was the best!  Ask for Yonas when you come in!

I had the bison Blue Creek burger, others had the bison ribs and the Ted’s Bacon Cheeseburger.  It was all delicious, including the vegetables. We were very happy with the food and the attention. The parking was good too. There’s free parking in front of the restaurant and paid ($8 flat fee) across the street.

My only complaint about the burger is that the bun was dry, felt kinda old. If the bun would be replaced it would be one of my favorites burgers.

Enjoyed my morning espresso here. Atmosphere is splendid. Quality of goods is top level. Staff is remarkable. Fine cup the coffee cake in. Thick enough to keep beverage hot but not too thick to eat it down. Great rim to sip off of.

They advertise The Bistro Dinner & Bar 5pm - 10 pm.  I reserved this hotel thinking that once I finished my day I could get dinner at the hotel once I am done.  The Bistro is not open AT ALL during these times.  Management needs to remove this from all advertisements.
It's only open for breakfast. And only has over priced pre-made "Starbucks" coffee.
Food was cooked to order and prepared quickly.  The workers were very patient and willing to make a custom order.  The atmosphere was casual and family friendly.
Nice people, good chicken, reasonable wait time = chill time with family!

Low-key, friendly little spot with efficient service and excellent food. The garlic bread they bring to the table is absolutely delicious, the wine list is shockingly inexpensive for this area, and entree portions are large. I’ve also been by for lunch sandwiches a few times and they are both huge and delicious. My only regret is that we waited this long to visit for dinner. We will be back!

This place was pretty cute, and I randomly met friends here for Restaurant Week for dinner. Place gets pretty busy on a Saturday night. I had the vegetable soup and grouper with fettuccine. I loved the fish because it was not too soft or hard and the soup was seasoned well. I also had the stuffed mushrooms, cheese bread, and calamari. The calamari could use some more seasoning, but otherwise, everything was great.  The sweet wine was bomb, especially because I don't do tart wine.

We were in the area over the weekend and decided to try this place based on the reviews. It was a pleasant experience. The service was great and the food was even better. I had the chicken piccata with pasta and my partner ordered the lasagna. They brought ice water to the table as soon as we sat down and finished our meal off with a few complimentary bite sized pieces of brownie. Would definitely recommend this place if you are ever in the area.

When I saw wow, I mean WOW! This place has really really good food, I ordered one of the specials with scallops and it was perfect. The prices are fair and the garlic bread is the best I’ve ever had! (And not to toot my own horn, but I’ve eaten a lot of garlic bread.) I would recommend this place to anyone, I’ll probably be back for lunch tomorrow.

This is a little hidden gym! For an authentic taste of Italy 🇮🇹 try Aldo's Italian Kitchen and always expect a warm Italian greeting by Aldo's owner Emanuele Cognetti who is ALWAYS working to prepare some mouthwatering delicacies. My personal favorite is the Fettuccine with Portebello - Sautéed mushrooms served with fettuccine pasta, artichokes, herbs, garlic oil. I have a hard time ordering anything else. 😋

One of the best Mexican food spot! Great price! Food was very delicious. I love my food spicy and they had the perfect spicy level. Salsa was one of the best I have ever tried. I will definitely going to come here more often. 👌

6 Stars here for a phenomenal Mexican Restaurant. Jose R was a great/friendly/quick server who made us feel very at home. Love this place and glad we found it! Burritos are huge and the ench red sauce delicious.

First time visit was this past Sunday, 9.25. Clean. Easy to move throughout the restaurant.  The women's room, was large and could easily accommodate a ♿️. Atmosphere was comfortable, with authentic and appropriate music playing throughout.  My daughter treated me to an early-Birthday lunch. I ordered the SOPES meal. Food was tasty without being  overly-seasoned.  Our server was pleasant and friendly.  WILL definitely VISIT again. Good amount of parking available, too.
Great service, ok food and prices. Happy hour included 5 dollar margaritas that were good. The dishes had potential, but the burnt bean taste just tainted our meals.
The food was good, nice ambience, good service but does depend on your server. The signature queso is amazing with any of the Chorizo dishes. This is my go to spot for Mexican food. Always enjoy!

Service was friendly and good but food was a poor value and subpar.
I got the steak and cheese and it was a sad tiny ok little sandwich for the price of 10.95 for a maybe 12”hoagie with scarce filling. I Paid extra (2.25)for the fries and they were overfried and scarce. $20 including tip was not worth the quality of this meal. I will not be back.

$8.00 for a can of a regular beer and no draft options! I will not return and apparently noone else does either as the place was all but empty at 6:00 p.m. on a nice winter Saturday evening.  I wish them well!

I'm a very tolerant person who doesn't mind many things. But I stood at the front waiting to be acknowledged for a good 10 minutes. 3 people saw me and none did anything to greet me. Finally an Asian lady came by and took my order. The interaction was weird. I had to reach over the counter to retrieve my card and receipt. Place was dirty and sticky. I ordered the chicken... It didn't slap. Their sauces were just subpar. I wish I had read the previous reviews before coming. Other customers coming in also felt lost asking me if I was in charge of the business. Saw a decent size group just leave. Poor customer service, dirty place, and food just isn't that good either.

I've ordered from Maggiano's in the past and the experience was quite good. However today's order was really really bad, the gyro meat was old, dry, and  overcooked to a crisp resembling jerky. The normally great Greek salad was not as fresh either.

Haven't been to the physical location but the food has been sensational every time I've ordered. They even removed the onions from the carbonate pasta when I didn't think they'd be able to. Delicious food, absolutely recommend.

Ordered 2 pizzas to take out , paid 39$ for 2 mediums pizza and both of them toppings were almost has nothing.
Ordered veggies pizza they have me Hawaiian pizza,
Didn't touch it so next day (today) took it with me to fix!
They really helped me and they gave veggies pizza but again A mistake, I asked white sauce instead of tomato  sauce but results a mistake.
Unfortunately can't have tomatoes because of allergy 😑
Employees are nice and friendly but

anyways

I think, universe and paisanos is telling me don't eat pizza !

Overpriced pizza delivered lukewarm.

EDIT:
- I could have eaten an entire “large” pizza myself.
- The pizza was delivered lukewarm.
- The menu lists extra toppings as $2.19, but after reviewing the bill, Spinach is actually $4.38.
- I called about this. Whoever answered told me this is inexplicably how it is, then hung up on me after explaining.
- The cheesecake was not appetizing and the extra strawberry was a mediocre glaze.
- My total bill was $42 after tip for pizza and cheesecake. Not worth it.

Order was delayed by 20 min due to one of the food items being “accidentally” included in another customer’s order. It would have been nice to be comped for the long delay, but just a quick apology was all I received. The only saving grace is that the front desk representative was very nice.

Maaan my steak and cheese were so delicious that I wanted to cry lol. I haven't had that taste in years. I was supposed to eat half and swallowed the whole thing. Try the steak and cheese when you go there. You won't regret it. I just wish they had specials or coupons to use. I probably would come more often if so.

The service is way better during the week. I just waited for 15 mins on the phone for the guy to take my order. Because I’m a regular customer my order pops up and the guys are able to repeat it. Whoever works on the weekend always lies and says that the system doesn’t work, therefore I have to repeat my order to him every freaking time. The fact that my order is usually ready in 10-15 mins is the main reason that I order from this place because that’s the time that it takes to get there. Having to be on hold to even give my order and then to have to wait in the parking lot for another 15-20 mins is annoying. Please get it together weekend crew.

I've never had bad Dominos Pizza before. Just drove 8 hrs and needed something quick for my daughter and I to eat for dinner. This was by far the worst pizza I've ever eaten. After tip, I spent $60 for a pizza that was like dry cardboard. I'm not sure what they did to this pizza. When I picked up a slice, the bottom fell off. It was like a burnt matzo cracker. There's barely any cheese. The brownies were burnt along the edges. Disappointing.
Get pizza from here at least twice a month. Only had a few not bad but not great experiences. Overall good experience with this Domino's.

Standard fare Domino's for me. I always order online and pick up in store. Most of the time, everything is fine. I've had missing sauces once or twice, and sometimes have had to wait longer than expected at the counter when picking up a prepaid order. Otherwise food is good and staff are decently friendly. I am a reoccurring customer.

Terrible experience on a large order. I ordered seven pizzas for an event two hours ahead of time, and the pizzas were not ready at the indicated pick-up time -- it was 10 minutes late. One of my three-topping pizzas was supposed to be pineapple, ham, and bacon, typical Hawaiian. Instead, I got pineapple, chicken, and jalapenos, not even close to what I ordered, and the combo tasted terrible. Finally for several of my pizzas they only cut into four slices instead of the eight they were supposed to, so it was impossible to separate for a large group. If you ever order from here, open up the pizzas and check -- it's very likely something isn't right, and they might be able to fix it before you get home to find multiple issues.

This is the worst dominos ever.  The lady just hung up on me.  We have waited for over an hour and half for our order.  One pizza and some breadsticks, (so not a huge order). They don't even deserve the one star.  Either they are lying to me at the store or the app is lying to me.  Either way I am being lied to about my order. The tracker says my order waited in quality check for 50 minutes. Then the app told me it was delivered and complete but I did not have my order.  When I called and told the lady about it, (yes I was mad and rightly so) she hung up me.  Terrible customer service. Which, unfortunalely, is the theme of the current day.  Customer service does not exist anymore and it definitely does not exist with the woman who answered the phone.  Still don't have pizza at this point and I bet its cold when it gets here!!!!!!!!!!!

The broth was flavourful and great tasting! I’m not a big fan of cartilage (there were tons of it in Combo 1), so I would’ve picked a difficult combo of cuts for the pho. But that’s tofu, beef, chicken slices were delicious. I do wish that more bean sprouts were offered (hence 4 stars), but everything else was great - food came quickly even though the restaurant was 3/4 packed. The hot tea, viet coffee and ice tea were 10/10. Their staff were also so friendly and kind!! They brought a styrofoam cup of water for our little one and offered a high chair for her even though we didn’t need it. Will definitely be back soon and more often!!

This is the best authentic pho I've had compared to what I've tried at other restaurants. I get the vege soup only (so can't speak for other items on the menu).  The soup has always been served fresh. It's served with toffu and vege meat. It's simple, relishing and satisfying. Regarding ambience, it's good for a casual laid back dinner/lunch. Staff are good people, especially the lady at the cashier counter. My fav Vietnamese restaurant so far.
Had some quality vermicelli the other night.  The portion of chicken vermicelli is enormous, and I had a great side of shrimp, with a coconut drink.  Gotta check this place out for authentic Pho!
